# Agent Instructions

This project is the **SystemHost** of the `{{ .name }}` Intropy integration
system: the single project that declares the system's components and the edges
between them, validates the topology, and hosts two backends over the same
discovered model — an Aspire run backend and a generation backend.

## Project overview

- Framework: .NET 10, Aspire AppHost
- System name: `{{ .name }}`
- System definition class: `{{ .systemClass }}` (the one `ISystemDefinition` in this assembly)
- Pub/sub component: `{{ .pubsub }}`
- Shared contracts project: `../{{ .projectName }}.Contracts`

## Important files

- `Program.cs` — entry point dispatching between the two backends. Do not edit.
- `{{ .systemClass }}.cs` — the `ISystemDefinition`: `Define(SystemBuilder)` declares
  every component and its edges. Generated by `intropy system create` from the
  sibling components' scaffold records; owned by you afterwards.
- `Topics.cs` / `Apis.cs` / `Connectors.cs` — the system's shared refs
  (`TopicRef<T>`, `ApiRef<T>`, `ConnectorRef`), declared as static fields.
- `../{{ .projectName }}.Contracts/Contracts.cs` — the contract records carried on
  topics and APIs, shared by this host and every component project.

## The folder convention

Each component declared in `Define()` resolves to a sibling project by name:
`../<component>/<component>.csproj`. Component name == folder name == csproj
name == Dapr app-id. Renaming any of these breaks the run backend.

## Build and run

```bash
dotnet run -- check              # validate the topology (do this after editing edges)
dotnet run -- graph              # print the SystemTopology JSON
dotnet run -- generate ./out     # write Dapr YAML + per-component runtime config
dotnet run                       # Aspire run backend (dashboard, Redis pub/sub, Dapr sidecars)
```

## Development notes

- Adding a component later: scaffold it as a sibling folder (`intropy int
  create block-*`), then add its `builder.Add<Kind>("<name>")` call and any new
  refs by hand — `Define()` is plain C#, and `dotnet run -- check` verifies the
  result.
- Contract records generated as empty stubs carry a
  `// TODO(intropy): define the payload` marker; fill them in as the
  components' real payloads take shape.
